  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Learning &amp; development for 200 children, Portugal</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will target at least 200 disadvantaged children in Portugal, who are at risk of dropping out of school or are having learning difficulties. The project uses living Nature as a learning, healing and development platform through alternative learning means such as equine-therapy, art-therapy, relaxation classes and nature-discovery activities. The project will also provide trainings for teachers and care-givers to assist them to use Nature as a source for alternative learning support.</narrative>
  </description>
